canonical:
  title: 安州送金政丞深上朝
  author: 李季瑊
  language: lzh
  text: 朔雪滿平野凍雲低古關聊將一盃酒出郭送征鞍
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 安州送金政丞深上朝
  author: 李季瑊
  language: lzh
  text: 朔雪滿平野。凍雲低古關。聊將一盃酒。出郭送征鞍。
korean:
  title: 안주에서 정승 김심이 중국에 사신 감을 전송하며
  author: 이계감
  language: kor
  text: |-
    차가운 눈은 평야에 가득하고
    언 구름은 옛 관문 위에 낮다
    애오라지 한 잔의 술로
    성곽을 나가 먼 길 행차를 보내노라
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0220_010_0400&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Farewell to Minister Kim Sim at Anjou, Sent on His Mission to the Capital
  author: Lee Gyejeam
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Snow fills the northern plain so cold,
    Frozen clouds hang low above the ancient gate.
    With nothing but a cup of wine in hand,
    I venture beyond the walls to bid farewell to his distant journey.
  footnotes:
    - The 'ancient gate' refers to a frontier pass, symbolizing the boundary between home and the unknown path ahead.
    - The single cup of wine represents the humble but sincere gesture of farewell, a common motif in East Asian poetry for seeing off travelers or officials on important missions.
